article.headline: Louisiana Tech rolls over Centenary, 106-59
article.story: RUSTON, La. -- Cordarius Johnson came off the bench to score 20 points as Louisiana Tech rolled over Centenary 106-59 on Wednesday night. Johnson was 7 of 13 and hit four from the 3-point line. He finished with 10 assists, two steals and a block. Starting forward Chris Anderson was 6 of 13 from the floor and had 18 points, six rebounds and one steal. He also hit 5 of 5 free throws. Raheem Appleby and Alex Hamilton chipped in 13 points each. Hamilton was also perfect from the free throw line, hitting 7 of 7. Overall, the Bulldogs sank 87.5 percent of their free throws and were 57 percent from the floor. Jonathan Blount led the Gentlemen with 6 of 13 shooting for 16 points. Centenary was held to just 20 points in the second half and were 34 percent from the floor overall.
